---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Marketing Apps for New Arrivals in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for new-arrival campaigns, early access, product discovery, inventory timing, and retention.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Brands with segmented launch audiences','Useful for category, VIP, browse, and engagement-based early access.','New-product data and inventory events need QA.','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation'],['Omnisend','Commerce teams launching collections','A practical fit for new arrivals, browse, cart, and coordinated channels.','Launch frequency and stock rules need governance.','https://www.omnisend.com/features/'],['Sequenzy','Editorial product launches','Good for a concise teaser, announcement, and product-education sequence.','Early-access and catalog integrations should be verified.','https://sequenzy.com/'],['Brevo','Campaign-led new-arrival programs','Useful when launches share infrastructure with newsletters and automation.','Product event mapping may require connectors.','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/'],['Shopify Email','Small catalogs with occasional launches','A simple native option for new-collection announcements.','Less suited to complex audience branches.','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email marketing apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">New-arrival email should help the right customer notice the right product at the right time. It should not become a repetitive broadcast every time a SKU changes.</p><p>Measure qualified product views, launch conversion, sell-through, full-price share, and unsubscribe rate. Use early access only when it is genuinely different, and suppress products that are unavailable or irrelevant to the subscriber’s expressed interests.</p><h2>Shortlist at a glance</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for new arrivals</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[2]}</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[0]} is useful when new-product messages can reflect category interest, access status, and actual stock. Build a launch path that moves from discovery to proof to purchase, then exits after the customer acts. New-arrival merchandising works best when the message offers a reason to care—not merely a date the product was added.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Check current contacts, sends, automation, catalog, and SMS limits; collection launches can create short-term volume spikes.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Need</th><th>Prioritize</th><th>Measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Discovery</td><td>Category and interest signals</td><td>Qualified product views</td></tr><tr><td>Access</td><td>Waitlist and VIP rules</td><td>Launch conversion</td></tr><tr><td>Economics</td><td>Stock and discount suppression</td><td>Full-price share</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Explore <a href="/alternatives">Shopify alternatives</a>, review <a href="/use-cases/product-launch">product-launch use cases</a>, or browse <a href="/apps">all Shopify email apps</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
